    "question": "Compare MLP, CNN, and RNN architectures.",
    "answer": "* **MLP (Multi-Layer Perceptron)**: Fully connected feedforward network. Every neuron connects to all neurons in next layer. Use for tabular data. Universal Approximation Theorem.\n* **CNN (Convolutional Neural Network)**: Uses convolutional filters for local pattern detection, pooling layers for dimensionality reduction, weight sharing to reduce parameters. Use for images, spatial data.\n* **RNN (Recurrent Neural Network)**: Feeds output back into itself, maintaining hidden state across time steps. Use for sequential data, time-series, text.",
