    "category": "genai_rag",
    "subcategory": "RAG",
    "question": "Compare Cosine Similarity, Dot Product, and L2 Distance for vector search.",
    "answer": "* **Cosine Similarity**: Measures angle between vectors, ignoring magnitude. Range [-1, 1]. Ideal when document lengths vary.\n* **Dot Product**: Measures both angle AND magnitude. Very fast. If vectors are normalized (magnitude=1), identical to cosine similarity.\n* **L2 (Euclidean) Distance**: Straight-line distance between vector endpoints. Smaller = more similar. Sensitive to vector magnitudes.\n* **Pre-filtering vs Post-filtering**:\n  - Post-filtering: Vector search first → then metadata filter. Risk: top-K may all get filtered out.\n  - Pre-filtering: Filter by metadata first → vector search on subset. Guarantees relevant results but requires metadata-aware index.",
    "is_coding": false,
    "code_sql": "",
    "code_java": "",
    "code_python": "",
    "id": 162
