    "category": "devops_projects",
    "subcategory": "System Design",
    "question": "What is caching? Explain caching strategies.",
    "answer": "Caching stores frequently accessed data in fast storage (memory) to reduce latency and database load.\n* **Strategies**:\n  1. **Cache-Aside (Lazy Loading)**: App checks cache first. On miss, fetches from DB, stores in cache. Most common.\n  2. **Write-Through**: Every write goes to cache AND database simultaneously. Consistent but slower writes.\n  3. **Write-Behind**: Write to cache only. Asynchronously batch-write to database. Fast writes but risk of data loss.\n  4. **Read-Through**: Cache automatically fetches from DB on miss. App only interacts with cache.\n* **Eviction policies**: LRU (Least Recently Used), LFU (Least Frequently Used), TTL (Time-To-Live).\n* **Tools**: Redis, Memcached.",
    "is_coding": false,
    "code_sql": "",
    "code_java": "",
    "code_python": "",
